@route_to_itaca

Route to Ítaca is about imagining how different could the 2010's have been for Catalonia, had things worked even so slightly differently. Its point is not to create a pro-independence fantasy, but rather, to serve as a tool to reflect on how far certain political movements got during the 2010's, and how further could they have gone. It's about the independence movement, but also about the anti-austerity struggles that plagued Europe, and many other street-born potentially revolutionary forces for change in the 21st century that ultimately folded into the status quo. What can hindsight provide, and what issues remain even then? Those are the enormous questions that (spoiler) will remain open even as you complete all the paths.

